Apply a thin layer to the affected skin areas two times daily, and rub in gently. Do not apply Locoid速 Lotion in the diaper area unless directed by a physician.
Discontinue therapy when control is achieved. If no improvement is seen within 2 weeks, reassessment of the diagnosis may be necessary. Before prescribing for more than 2 weeks, any additional benefits of extending treatment to 4 weeks should be weighed against the risk of HPA axis  suppression and local adverse events. The safety and efficacy of Locoid速 Lotion has not been established beyond 4 weeks of use [see WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS].
Do not use Locoid速 Lotion with occlusive dressings unless directed by a physician. Avoid use in the diaper area, as diapers or plastic pants ma y constitute occlusive dressings .
Locoid速 Lotion is not for oral, ophthalmic, or intravaginal use.
